# Command /organize-rules

When the user types **`/organize-rules`**, run the rule organization script to separate command files from rule files across all projects.

## What It Does

Scans every project under `$env:OptPath\src` (default `C:\opt\src`) for `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files and classifies each as a **Command** or a **Rule** based on filename and description. Command files are moved into a `Commands/` subfolder within each project's `.cursor/rules/`.

## Classification Criteria

A `.mdc` file is a **Command** if any of the following match:

| Signal | Example |
|--------|---------|
| Filename starts with `command-` | `command-commit.mdc` |
| Filename is `commands.mdc` | `commands.mdc` |
| Filename starts with `chat-command-` | `chat-command-test.mdc` |
| Description contains `Command /` | `"Command /autocur: ..."` |
| Description contains `When user says/types/enters /` | `"When user says /commit, ..."` |
| Description says `Custom commands` | `"Custom Cursor commands"` |
| Description matches workflow trigger with `/` and `run` | `"When user says /publish, run Build-And-Publish.ps1"` |

Everything else is a **Rule** and stays at the `.cursor/rules/` root level.

## How to Run

```powershell
# Preview (no changes)
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\CursorRulesLibrary\Scripts\Organize-CursorRules.ps1" -WhatIf

# Execute
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\CursorRulesLibrary\Scripts\Organize-CursorRules.ps1"

# Single project only
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\CursorRulesLibrary\Scripts\Organize-CursorRules.ps1" -ProjectName AutoDocJson
```

## Duplicate Handling

If a file already exists in `Commands/` (e.g. from a previous run or manual move):
- **Identical content**: the root-level copy is deleted (dedup)
- **Different content**: skipped with a warning for manual merge
